# Description:
# Script to analyze the frames of a loaded Siril sequence and plot key statistics
# (Min, Max, Mean, Median, Std Dev) for each frame, with support for deviation analysis.
#
# Features:
# - Detects whether a sequence is loaded, and can load one from the working directory.
# - Reads only the frames currently marked as “included” in the sequence (Frame List Selector).
# - Supports MONO, RGB, and CFA sequences (channel extraction based on FITS headers).
# - Calculates per-frame statistics: Min, Max, Mean, Median, and Standard Deviation.
# - Plots statistics as interactive graphs with tooltips and selectable curves.
# - Provides two analysis modes:
#   • Absolute statistics (raw values per frame).
#   • Deviation from global median (percentage), with optional outlier highlighting.
# - Outlier detection using robust metrics (MAD-based), with visual highlights on the graph.
# 
# 
# Versions:
# 1.0.0 - Initial release
# 1.0.1 - added processing_thread to avoid GUI freeze on Large Sequences
#

